    <note type="biography">
        <p>German-born painter and illustrator. Specialised in animals. Apprenticed as a lithographer in Koblenz before studying art at the Antwerp Academy. Arrived in London in 1848. Established a studio with Johann Baptist Zwecker in London, <hi rend="italic">circa</hi> 1860. Illustrated many natural history publications including Henry Walter Bates’s <hi rend="italic">The naturalist on the river Amazons</hi> (1863).</p></note>
